  "body": "### Description\r\nAs a Validator, I want to be able to specify the value of extraData in the execution blocks that I propose\r\n\r\n### Acceptance Criteria\r\n* Update existing pre-merge command line options and configuration to work in the post-merge world OR\r\n* Provide new post-merge options that allow this value to be set e.g. `--validator-extra-data`\r\n\r\n### Steps to Reproduce (Bug)\r\n1. Configure a validator\r\n2. Use existing `--miner-extra-data` or `miner-extra-data` config to set extraData in blocks built by Besu\r\n3. Propose a block\r\n4. See block proposed with null extraData field\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:** The value specified in the miner-extra-data configuration should make its way into the block's extraData field.\r\n\r\n**Actual behavior:** The extraData field is null in the block.\r\n\r\n**Frequency:** 100%\r\n\r\n### Versions (Add all that apply)\r\n* Software version: besu/v22.7.4/linux-x86_64/oracle-java-18\r\n* Java version: Java(TM) SE Runtime Environment (build 18.0.2+9-61)\r\n* OS Name & Version: Arch Linux\r\n* Kernel Version: 5.19.12-arch1-1\r\n\r\n### Additional Information (Add any of the following or anything else that may be relevant)\r\n* System info - 16GB Memory, Quad core i5-3570\r\n",
